data.comment: The first-half is just kicking off.
Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 1, Glenn Nyberg awards the away team a throw-in.
Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Ball goes out of play for a Malmo goal kick.
In the minute 4, Malmo pushes forward through Soren Rieks, whose finish on goal is saved.
Jonathan Ring for Djurgarden drives towards goal at Tele2 Arena. But the finish is unsuccessful.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
In the minute 7, Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Malmo awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Malmo are pushing forward but Adi Nalic's finish is wide of the goal.
In the minute 9, It's a goal kick for the home team in Stockholm.
Malmo drives forward and Adi Nalic gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
Throw-in high up the field for Malmo in Stockholm.
In the minute 10, Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
Throw-in for Malmo at Tele2 Arena.
Malmo's Adi Nalic is on target but unsuccessful.
In the minute 14, Malmo awarded a free kick in their own half.
Malmo's Soren Rieks gets in a shot on goal at Tele2 Arena. But the effort is unsuccessful.
Throw-in for Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 17, Malmo's Erdal Rakip breaks free at Tele2 Arena. But the strike goes wide of the post.
Djurgarden have a goal kick.
Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 18, Ola Toivonen scores to make it 0-1 at Tele2 Arena.
Jo Inge Berget with an assist there.
Glenn Nyberg signals a Djurgarden throw-in in Malmo's half.
In the minute 21, Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
In Stockholm, Djurgarden push forward quickly but are pulled up for offside.
In the minute 25, Ball safe as Djurgarden is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Djurgarden's Nicklas Barkroth has been booked in Stockholm.
Free kick Malmo.
In the minute 29, Malmo have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Corner awarded to Malmo.
Goal kick for Djurgarden at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 30, Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden.
Jo Inge Berget for Malmo has been booked by Glenn Nyberg and receives a first yellow card.
Haris Radetinac for Djurgarden has been booked by Glenn Nyberg and will miss the next match due to a suspension.
In the minute 33, Throw-in Malmo.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 35, Ball safe as Djurgarden is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
Anders Christiansen of Malmo smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
In the minute 37, Glenn Nyberg signals a throw-in for Malmo, close to Djurgarden's area.
Corner awarded to Malmo.
Malmo have a dangerous throw-in.
In the minute 38, Glenn Nyberg awards Djurgarden a goal kick.
Free kick for Malmo in the half of Djurgarden.
Malmo awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 40, Can Malmo get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Djurgarden's half?
Throw-in for Djurgarden in their own half.
Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 43, Djurgarden are too eager and fall into an offside trap.
Malmo have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Ball goes out of play for a Djurgarden goal kick.
In the minute 45, Throw-in for Malmo in the half of Djurgarden.
Glenn Nyberg awards the home team a throw-in.
Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 45, 1 minutes will be added to the 1st half in Stockholm.
Throw-in Djurgarden.
In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In the minute 45, The first-half is over.
Glenn Nyberg has blown to start the second-half.
Throw-in for Malmo at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 46, Malmo are whistled for offside.
Corner awarded to Malmo.
Throw-in for Malmo in the half of Djurgarden.
In the minute 50, Djurgarden's Nicklas Barkroth has run offside.
Glenn Nyberg signals a Malmo throw-in in Djurgarden's half.
Malmo's Adi Nalic gets his shot away but it misses the target.
In the minute 54, It's a goal kick for the home team in Stockholm.
Free kick Djurgarden.
In the minute 55, Glenn Nyberg awards Malmo a goal kick.
The home team replace Jonathan Ring with Edward Chilufya.
In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In Stockholm Djurgarden attack through Jonathan Augustinsson. The finish is off target, however.
In the minute 57, Malmo have a goal kick.
Free kick for Malmo in the half of Djurgarden.
Adi Nalic of Malmo gets in a strike, but is off target.
In the minute 58, Goal kick for Djurgarden at Tele2 Arena.
Glenn Nyberg waits before resuming play because Jesper Nyholm for Djurgarden is still down.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
In the minute 60, Jesper Nyholm has recovered and rejoins the match in Stockholm.
Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Jesper Karlstrom (Djurgarden) goes for goal but the shot is blocked by an alert defence.
In the minute 61, Edward Chilufya (Djurgarden) is given an opening but the shot is blocked by a defender.
Malmo have a goal kick.
Can Malmo get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Djurgarden's half?
In the minute 62, It's now 0-2 in Stockholm as Ola Toivonen scores for Malmo.
Jonas Knudsen instrumental with a fine assist.
Attention is being given to Djurgardenâ€™s Jesper Nyholm and play has been suspended briefly.
In the minute 64, Elliot Kack (Djurgarden) has replaced the possibly injured Jesper Nyholm at Tele2 Arena.
Djurgarden make their third substitution with Kalle Holmberg replacing Nicklas Barkroth.
Jon Dahl Tomasson is making the team's first substitution at Tele2 Arena with Arnor Traustason replacing Jo Inge Berget.
In the minute 65, Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Malmo.
Free kick Malmo.
Magnus Eriksson (Djurgarden) has received a yellow card from Glenn Nyberg.
In the minute 67, It's a goal kick for the home team in Stockholm.
Free kick in a good position for Djurgarden!
Franz Brorsson (Malmo) gets a yellow card.
In the minute 71, Malmo awarded a free kick in their own half.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 73, Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
Anders Christiansen is booked for the away team.
Ball safe as Djurgarden is awarded a throw-in in their half.
In the minute 75, At Tele2 Arena, Jacob Une Larsson has been yellow-carded for the home team.
Djurgarden drive upfield and Haris Radetinac gets in a shot. The strike is blocked by a Malmo defender.
Amin Sarr is on a sub for Adi Nalic for Malmo.
Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
In the minute 78, Samuel Adrian is replacing Anders Christiansen for Malmo at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 79, Ball goes out of play for a Malmo goal kick.
Thomas Lagerlof (Djurgarden) is making a fourth substitution, with Curtis Edwards replacing Magnus Eriksson.
Mattias Mitku is replacing Haris Radetinac for the home team.
In the minute 81, Important block from the Malmo defence as Fredrik Ulvestad fires in a strike for Djurgarden.
Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
Fredrik Ulvestad (Djurgarden) heads in to reduce the deficit. The score is now 1-2.
In the minute 81, Great play from Elliot Kack to set up the goal.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
Goal! Kalle Holmberg levels the match at 2-2.
In the minute 83, Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
Isaac Thelin is replacing Soren Rieks for the away team.
Malmo have been awarded a corner by Glenn Nyberg.
In the minute 85, Throw-in Djurgarden.
Glenn Nyberg awards the away team a throw-in.
Djurgarden awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In the minute 87, Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
Can Djurgarden get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Malmo's half?
Throw-in for Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 89, Goal! The home team take a 3-2 lead through Kalle Holmberg.
That's a fine assist from Edward Chilufya.
6 minutes will be added to the 2nd half.
Throw-in for Djurgarden at Tele2 Arena.
Malmo awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Throw-in Malmo.
Kalle Holmberg for Djurgarden is back on the field again.
Corner awarded to Malmo.
Malmo are caught offside.
Glenn Nyberg awards Malmo a goal kick.
Glenn Nyberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden.
Djurgarden to take a throw-in in Malmo territory.
Glenn Nyberg blows to end the match. The final score is 3-2.
Kalle Holmberg is writhing in pain and play has been suspended for a few moments.
Arnor Traustason (Malmo) has been booked and must now be careful not to get a second yellow card.
